{
  "stem": "26142.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and once they got into the Tisza, the Tisza River fell into the Danube.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Danube already across, went all the way to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's how-- that was the-- this was a business that-- that-- it was seasonal.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Winter time, you had to cut the trees in the summer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But you couldn't take it out in the summer from the forests.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Winter, when the snow-- the snow was-- on the ground, and the Carpathians especially, we had a long-- long winter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we would-- we would hire people with horses and even people that have oxen and sleighs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And to bring that lumber out-- and they would put it alongside-- we had ports, like my father had, that would lay it out alongside the River Riga.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then in the summer time, we hired laborers to-- to tie these together.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, they were launched, put into the water.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And of course, in the summer time, sometimes when there was no rain, you couldn't-- the-- the waters were not-- not big enough.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And one year, I think in the '30s, they built a dam, and-- and collected water so that they can release water whenever they need it in order to-- to be able to ship it [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But this was the-- the-- the main industry.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was-- I was too young-- too, too young.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The only-- the only thing that I-- I knew about was I used to love to be on the-- on the-- on the saw mill work.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's where they-- where they cut logs and-- and cut them in boards.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then they split-- split them, make two by twos or two by fours, or whatever they-- they worked it up.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That-- and that was-- that was a water-- water-driven mill.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
